issue.body:
I'm using EFCore 7.

I have a ef core model likes below, the column `Address` that allows json string or null:
```csharp
  modelBuilder.Entity<User>(e =>
  {
      e.OwnsOne(p => p.Address, b => b.ToJson());
  });

public partial class User
{
    [StringLength(50)]
    [Unicode(false)]
    public string Name { get; set; } = null!;
    ...
    public UserAddress? Address { get; set; } = null!;
}
```

And I faced two questions:

1. When I executed the query likes below:
```csharp
_labDBContext.Users.Select(x => new Model_User()
{
    Name = x.Name,
     ...
    UserAddress = x.Address
}).ToList();
```
I would get error message `variable '' of type 'IScom_Test_API.Models.DBModels.LabDB.UserAddress' referenced from scope '', but it is not defined`

but if I change to the code as below, it will work as expected:
```csharp
_labDBContext.Users.Select(x => new Model_User()
{
    Name = x.Name,
     ...
    UserAddress = new()
    {
        City = x.Address.City,
        Country = x.Address.Country
    }
}).ToList();
```
I'm not sure if there's any problem or limitation about EFCore's `Select` function or not?

2. And I have another code as below, the same, want to select or filter the IQuerable variable with a json column `Address`:
```csharp
_labDBContext.Users.Where(x => x.Address == null).ToList();
```

It'll also return the errors, 
`Error creating query string: The LINQ expression 'DbSet<User>()
    .Where(u => EF.Property<UserAddress>(u, "Address") == null)' could not be translated. Either rewrite the query in a form that can be translated, or switch to client evaluation explicitly by inserting a call to 'AsEnumerable', 'AsAsyncEnumerable', 'ToList', or 'ToListAsync'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2101038 for more information..`
    
I think the reasons that caused the two questions are similar, does anyone knows why would it  cause error if I want to manipulate a json column?
